{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SisYs2mGvpsHnZNXYBn119","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully gathered all the source code related to the `cloche logs` command. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: `cloche logs` Command Implementation\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition (`cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 347-450)\n\nThe `cmdLogs` function is the main entry point. Here are the **flags that exist**:\n\n- **`--step, -s <name>`** - Filter logs to a specific step\n- **`--type <full|script|llm>`** - Filter by log type (full, script, or llm output)\n- **`--follow, -f`** - Stream logs in real time (follow mode, like `tail -f`)\n- **`--limit, -l <n>`** - Display only the last n lines of output\n\n**Implementation details:**\n- The CLI passes `follow` and `limit` via gRPC metadata headers (`x-cloche-follow` and `x-cloche-limit`) rather than in the protobuf message itself\n- Follow mode uses background context (since log output can be large and blocks)\n- The command calls `client.StreamLogs()` with the run ID, step filter, and log type\n\n### 2. Help Text (`cmd/cloche/help.go`, lines 111-141)\n\nComplete help documentation for the logs command:\n- Explains all flags clearly\n- Shows that flags are combinable\n- Provides practical examples demonstrating usage patterns\n\n### 3. gRPC Proto Definition (`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`, lines 62-78)\n\n**`StreamLogsRequest` message:**\n```protobuf\nmessage StreamLogsRequest {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string log_type = 3;\n  bool follow = 4;      // (passed via metadata header \"x-cloche-follow\")\n  int32 limit = 5;      // (passed via metadata header \"x-cloche-limit\")\n}\n```\n\n**`LogEntry` response message:**\n```protobuf\nmessage LogEntry {\n  string type = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string result = 3;\n  string message = 4;\n  string timestamp = 5;\n}\n```\n\nThe proto file includes comments noting that `follow` and `limit` are currently passed via gRPC metadata headers (not in the proto message itself).\n\n### 4. Server-Side Implementation (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 488-764)\n\n**Main `StreamLogs` function (lines 488-599):**\n- Extracts follow mode and limit from gRPC metadata using `followFromContext()` and `limitFromContext()`\n- Handles three main scenarios:\n  1. **Filtered logs** (by step/type): calls `streamFilteredLogs()`\n  2. **Follow mode on active run**: calls `streamFollowLogs()` - combines snapshot + live streaming\n  3. **Regular mode**: sends snapshot of existing logs or full.log file\n\n**Helper functions:**\n\n- **`followFromContext()` (lines 602-609)**: Reads `x-cloche-follow` metadata header\n- **`limitFromContext()` (lines 612-627)**: Reads `x-cloche-limit` metadata header, returns integer\n- **`applyLimit()` (lines 630-643)**: Extracts last n lines from content (used by both modes)\n- **`streamFollowLogs()` (lines 647-694)**: Implements follow mode - subscribes to log broadcaster, sends existing logs first, then tails live output\n- **`streamFilteredLogs()` (lines 698-764)**: Serves logs filtered by step name and/or log type, using the log index when available\n\n**Log entry types sent to client:**\n- `\"step_started\"` - Step beginning\n- `\"step_completed\"` - Step completion with result\n- `\"run_completed\"` - Run terminal state\n- `\"full_log\"` - Complete unfiltered output\n- `\"log\"` - Live-streamed log line\n- Type-specific entries like `\"script_log\"`, `\"llm_log\"`, etc.\n\n### File Paths for Reference\n\n- **CLI command**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Help text**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`\n- **gRPC proto**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- **Server implementation**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a9e36824586627b20 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 52353\ntool_uses: 11\nduration_ms: 17399</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"c5dff30f-5fc8-497c-a38d-136825980825","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find all source code related to the `cloche logs` command implementation. Look for:\n1. The CLI command definition and flags for `logs` in cmd/cloche/\n2. Any gRPC proto definitions related to logs\n3. Any server-side implementation of logs in internal/adapters/grpc/\n4. The help.go file for CLI help text\n\nRead the full contents of each relevant file. I need to understand what flags exist for `cloche logs` (especially -f/--follow, -s/--step, -l/--limit) and how they're implemented.","agentId":"a9e36824586627b20","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have successfully gathered all the source code related to the `cloche logs` command. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: `cloche logs` Command Implementation\n\n### 1. CLI Command Definition (`cmd/cloche/main.go`, lines 347-450)\n\nThe `cmdLogs` function is the main entry point. Here are the **flags that exist**:\n\n- **`--step, -s <name>`** - Filter logs to a specific step\n- **`--type <full|script|llm>`** - Filter by log type (full, script, or llm output)\n- **`--follow, -f`** - Stream logs in real time (follow mode, like `tail -f`)\n- **`--limit, -l <n>`** - Display only the last n lines of output\n\n**Implementation details:**\n- The CLI passes `follow` and `limit` via gRPC metadata headers (`x-cloche-follow` and `x-cloche-limit`) rather than in the protobuf message itself\n- Follow mode uses background context (since log output can be large and blocks)\n- The command calls `client.StreamLogs()` with the run ID, step filter, and log type\n\n### 2. Help Text (`cmd/cloche/help.go`, lines 111-141)\n\nComplete help documentation for the logs command:\n- Explains all flags clearly\n- Shows that flags are combinable\n- Provides practical examples demonstrating usage patterns\n\n### 3. gRPC Proto Definition (`api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`, lines 62-78)\n\n**`StreamLogsRequest` message:**\n```protobuf\nmessage StreamLogsRequest {\n  string run_id = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string log_type = 3;\n  bool follow = 4;      // (passed via metadata header \"x-cloche-follow\")\n  int32 limit = 5;      // (passed via metadata header \"x-cloche-limit\")\n}\n```\n\n**`LogEntry` response message:**\n```protobuf\nmessage LogEntry {\n  string type = 1;\n  string step_name = 2;\n  string result = 3;\n  string message = 4;\n  string timestamp = 5;\n}\n```\n\nThe proto file includes comments noting that `follow` and `limit` are currently passed via gRPC metadata headers (not in the proto message itself).\n\n### 4. Server-Side Implementation (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`, lines 488-764)\n\n**Main `StreamLogs` function (lines 488-599):**\n- Extracts follow mode and limit from gRPC metadata using `followFromContext()` and `limitFromContext()`\n- Handles three main scenarios:\n  1. **Filtered logs** (by step/type): calls `streamFilteredLogs()`\n  2. **Follow mode on active run**: calls `streamFollowLogs()` - combines snapshot + live streaming\n  3. **Regular mode**: sends snapshot of existing logs or full.log file\n\n**Helper functions:**\n\n- **`followFromContext()` (lines 602-609)**: Reads `x-cloche-follow` metadata header\n- **`limitFromContext()` (lines 612-627)**: Reads `x-cloche-limit` metadata header, returns integer\n- **`applyLimit()` (lines 630-643)**: Extracts last n lines from content (used by both modes)\n- **`streamFollowLogs()` (lines 647-694)**: Implements follow mode - subscribes to log broadcaster, sends existing logs first, then tails live output\n- **`streamFilteredLogs()` (lines 698-764)**: Serves logs filtered by step name and/or log type, using the log index when available\n\n**Log entry types sent to client:**\n- `\"step_started\"` - Step beginning\n- `\"step_completed\"` - Step completion with result\n- `\"run_completed\"` - Run terminal state\n- `\"full_log\"` - Complete unfiltered output\n- `\"log\"` - Live-streamed log line\n- Type-specific entries like `\"script_log\"`, `\"llm_log\"`, etc.\n\n### File Paths for Reference\n\n- **CLI command**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go`\n- **Help text**: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go`\n- **gRPC proto**: `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`\n- **Server implementation**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":17399,"totalTokens":52353,"totalToolUseCount":11,"usage":{"input_tokens":7,"cache_creation_input_tokens":35918,"cache_read_input_tokens":15344,"output_tokens":1084,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":35918},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
