{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01X39tUhxFjzAhiJaof3xvLs","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of all the documentation I've found. Here's my findings:\n\n## Documentation Files Found - Summary Report\n\nI've located and read all documentation files that reference the `cloche logs` command and CLI commands in general. Here are the relevant files:\n\n### Primary Documentation Files:\n\n1. **/workspace/CLAUDE.md** (Line 19)\n   - Lists `logs` as a CLI subcommand\n   - Part of the architecture overview\n\n2. **/workspace/docs/USAGE.md** (Lines 687-699)\n   - **Complete CLI Reference for `cloche logs`:**\n     - Syntax: `cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]`\n     - Flags:\n       - `--step <name>` — Show only logs for specified step\n       - `--type <full|script|llm>` — Log type filter\n       - `-f` — Follow mode (like `tail -f`)\n     - Behavior: Without `-f` displays all logs and exits; with `-f` on active run, streams new output in real-time via gRPC until run completes\n\n3. **/workspace/docs/plans/2026-02-20-cloche-system-design.md** (Line 29)\n   - Lists `logs` as one of the CLI subcommands\n   - Describes it as: \"Stream logs from a running workflow (bidirectional gRPC stream)\"\n\n4. **/workspace/docs/agent-setup-claude.md** (Lines 101-104)\n   - Usage example: `cloche logs <run-id>`\n   - Mentioned in context of verifying Claude Code setup\n\n5. **/workspace/docs/agent-setup-codex.md** (Lines 119-122)\n   - Usage example: `cloche logs <run-id>`\n   - Mentioned in context of verifying Codex setup\n\n6. **/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-03-next-features-design.md** (Lines 177-224)\n   - Detailed design for Log Contents feature\n   - CLI enhancements include:\n     - `cloche logs <run-id>` — shows full unified log\n     - `cloche logs <run-id> --step <name>` — filters to specific step\n     - `cloche logs <run-id> --follow