{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019PLrrYYsHZ6hptpA19QmH9","type":"tool_result","content":"   680→|------|-------------|\n   681→| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n   682→| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n   683→| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n   684→| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n   685→| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n   686→\n   687→### `cloche logs`\n   688→\n   689→```\n   690→cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n   691→```\n   692→\n   693→| Flag | Description |\n   694→|------|-------------|\n   695→| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n   696→| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n   697→| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n   698→\n   699→Without `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n   700→\n   701→### `cloche poll`\n   702→\n   703→```\n   704→cloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n   705→```\n   706→\n   707→Block until all specified runs finish. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 if all runs succeeded, 1 if any failed or were cancelled.\n   708→\n   709→With a single run ID, prints step-level progress. With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary (e.g. `id1: running`) and re-prints whenever a state changes. Use `cloche logs` for detailed output of individual runs."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"9744f40d-64c0-4508-a3a7-ed2a2f3624c0","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","content":"|------|-------------|\n| `--all` | Show runs from all projects (default: current project only). |\n| `--project, -p DIR` | Filter by project directory. |\n| `--state, -s STATE` | Filter by run state (`pending`, `running`, `succeeded`, `failed`, `cancelled`). |\n| `--limit, -n NUM` | Limit the number of results returned. |\n| `--issue, -i ID` | Filter by issue/task ID. |\n\n### `cloche logs`\n\n```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.\n\n### `cloche poll`\n\n```\ncloche poll <run-id> [run-id...]\n```\n\nBlock until all specified runs finish. Polls every 2 seconds. Exits 0 if all runs succeeded, 1 if any failed or were cancelled.\n\nWith a single run ID, prints step-level progress. With multiple run IDs, displays a compact status summary (e.g. `id1: running`) and re-prints whenever a state changes. Use `cloche logs` for detailed output of individual runs.","numLines":30,"startLine":680,"totalLines":922}}}
