{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MhkZ1WEfFYTEf29YzTaRF5","type":"tool_result","content":"   111→\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n   112→\n   113→Streams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\n   114→step name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n   115→\n   116→Usage:\n   117→  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n   118→\n   119→Arguments:\n   120→  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n   121→\n   122→Flags:\n   123→  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n   124→  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n   125→                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n   126→                                   script  — script/command output only\n   127→                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n   128→  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n   129→                                 run completes or is stopped).\n   130→  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n   131→\n   132→Flags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n   133→\n   134→Examples:\n   135→  cloche logs abc123\n   136→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n   137→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n   138→  cloche logs abc123 -f\n   139→  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n   140→  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n   141→`,\n   142→\n   143→\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n   144→\n   145→Polls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"80e1ce2e-a764-409e-b43f-733763e5218d","uuid":"e50d1dce-6fcb-4f18-ab7a-8cb4e0c12dd4","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/cmd/cloche/help.go","content":"\t\"logs\": `cloche logs — Show logs for a run\n\nStreams or displays log output for a workflow run. Supports filtering by\nstep name and log type, limiting output, and following live output.\n\nUsage:\n  cloche logs <run-id> [-s <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n\nArguments:\n  <run-id>    The run identifier.\n\nFlags:\n  --step, -s <name>              Show logs only for the named step.\n  --type <full|script|llm>       Filter by log type:\n                                   full    — complete unfiltered output\n                                   script  — script/command output only\n                                   llm     — LLM interaction logs only\n  --follow, -f                   Stream logs in real time (blocks until the\n                                 run completes or is stopped).\n  --limit, -l <n>                Display only the last n lines of output.\n\nFlags are combinable: cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f\n\nExamples:\n  cloche logs abc123\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20\n  cloche logs abc123 -f\n  cloche logs abc123 -s test --type script\n  cloche logs abc123 -s implement -l 20 -f\n`,\n\n\t\"poll\": `cloche poll — Wait for runs to finish\n\nPolls the daemon every 2 seconds until all runs reach a terminal state","numLines":35,"startLine":111,"totalLines":477}}}
