{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01921nmY6dZX4cUEw98vREwM","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01WsQx4Ev2sFVqE3o8wEHNgs","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/workspace/docs/USAGE.md","old_string":"```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `-f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes.","new_string":"```\ncloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [-f] [-l <n>]\n```\n\n| Flag | Description |\n|------|-------------|\n| `--step, -s <name>` | Show only logs for the specified step. |\n| `--type <full\\|script\\|llm>` | Log type filter. |\n| `--follow, -f` | Follow mode: display existing logs then continue streaming new lines as they arrive (like `tail -f`). |\n| `--limit, -l <n>` | Display only the last n lines of output. |\n\nFlags are combinable: `cloche logs run-id -s implement -l 20 -f`\n\nWithout `-f`, displays all logs captured to date and exits (even for active runs). With `-f` on an active run, existing logs are sent first, then new output is streamed in real time via gRPC until the run completes."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1398,"cache_read_input_tokens":19491,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1398},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"